condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :PA-I.C.3 | Description :Monitor compliance with the RAP and EMP on expressway and interconnecting roads; providerecommendations to enhance compliance within 30 days of each semi-annual review | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA-II.A.1 | Description :Submit project reports measuring program indicators within 30 days of that period's end| Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA-II.B.2 | Description :Provide interim unaudited financial reports covering the calendar semester period ofeach Project Report within 30 days of that period's end | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA-IV.1 | Description :Prepare and implement RAP, EIA, and EMP prior to any construction activities | Due Date:30-Jun-2009
Finance Agreement :PA-IV.2 | Description :Arrange to supervise civil works and compliance with EMP by separate consultants, priorto construction | Due Date :30-Jun-2009
Finance Agreement :PA-IV.3 | Description :Implement measures for securing compliance with EMP and RAP, and specify sanctions forfailure to carry out requirements | Due Date :30-Jun-2009
